Program: Thinking Allowed
Title: Hospices - Palliative Care
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b099ypqf
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 30 Oct 2017
Palliative medicine and care: Laurie Taylor talks to David Clarke, Professor of Medical Sociology at the University of Glasgow, about his social history of 'easeful death'. Also, daily life in an English Hospice. Danny Miller, Professor of Anthropology at UCL, explores kinship, loneliness and community amongst people suffering from terminal or long term illness. Producer: Jayne Egerton. Show less